				<div class="toggles accordion toggles--minimal-shadow" data-br="none" data-starting="default" data-style="minimal"><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="nectar-inherit-h3 toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>What is the Custom Occupation Report?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>The Custom Occupation Report allows migration professionals to generate a detailed, professional-grade report for any occupation in the ANZSCO catalogue. You can choose which sections and visa pathways to include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Skilled visas</strong> (Subclass 189, 190, 491)</li>
<li><strong data-start="394" data-end="440">State and Territory nomination eligibility</strong></li>
<li><strong>Employer-Sponsored visas</strong> (subclass 482, 186, 494)</li>
<li><strong>DAMA Eligibility</strong></li>
<li><strong>Graduate visa</strong> (subclass 485)</li>
<li><strong>Visa Eligibility Summary</strong></li>
<li><strong>Backlog Overview </strong>(SkillSelect EOIs)</li>
<li><strong>ANZSCO Information Sheet</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>Each report is generated as a branded, ready-to-share PDF for your clients.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>Who can use the Custom Occupation Report?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>This tool is designed for registered migration agents, Australian legal practitioners, and migration professionals who require accurate, branded client documentation.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="nectar-inherit-h3 toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>What’s included in the report?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>Anzscosearch offers a <strong>Tailored Report</strong> built around specific client scenarios. A flexible format where each report can include any combination of the following sections:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Eligibility Summary Report</strong>: A concise summary showing: <strong>ANZSCO eligibility </strong>across Skilled (189, 190, 491), Employer-Sponsored (482, 186, 494) and Graduate (485) pathways. Ideal for a quick, professional summary combining eligibility and occupation details in one document.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Visa Requirements (Overview &amp; Key Criteria) and ANZSCO Eligibility </strong>– concise pages outlining how each program works and the headline criteria:</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none">
<ul>
<li>Skilled (Points-tested): age threshold, occupation on the relevant list, positive skills assessment, Competent English, points score met at invitation, and invitation required; plus, the key differences between 189/190/491.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none">
<ul>
<li>State / Territory Eligibility. Nomination pathways by state or territory.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none">
<ul>
<li>Employer-Sponsored: nomination fundamentals (genuine full-time role, eligible occupation), AMSR and minimum salary thresholds (e.g. TSMIT/CSIT/SSIT), and LMT where required; plus, streams (482, 186, 494) and when skills assessment or “Competent/Vocational English” apply.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none">
<ul>
<li>Designated Area Migration Agreement (DAMA) eligibility.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none">
<ul>
<li>Graduate (485): streams (Post-Vocational and Post-Higher Education), core settings (age, English benchmark, when a skills assessment is required), and the Australian Study Requirement elements.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Professional Advice</strong> – a dedicated space to add your own comments/recommendations (or leave it blank).</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Backlog Overview</strong> – a snapshot of current SkillSelect EOIs by points band and status (Submitted, Invited, Lodged), providing a clear view of competition and invitation pressure for the nominated occupation.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>ANZSCO Information Sheet </strong>– occupation description, tasks, assessing authority, indicative skill level, and any listed specialisations.</li>
</ul>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>Does the report include State and Territory nomination eligibility and criteria?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>The report includes a <strong>high-level overview of State and Territory nomination eligibility</strong>, showing whether an occupation is listed for nomination and which pathways or streams may apply across each jurisdiction.</p>
<p>However, <strong>detailed State and Territory nomination criteria and requirements are not included</strong>. These requirements are extensive, frequently updated, and vary significantly between jurisdictions and pathways. Including full criteria for every State and Territory would substantially increase the length and complexity of the report and undermine its purpose of providing a clear, client-friendly summary.</p>
<p>To ensure accuracy, the report <strong>includes links to the official State and Territory websites</strong>, allowing users to <strong>access the most current nomination requirements</strong> directly from the original sources.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>How long is the report?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>The length of each report depends on the sections you select. A simple ANZSCO Information Sheet is usually <strong>4–5 pages</strong>, while a fully customised report that includes all visa pathways and sections can extend to around <strong>20–22 pages</strong>.</p>
<p>The final length may also vary depending on whether you include professional advice or comments. The Professional Advice section allows up to <strong>1,000 words</strong> (around 6,500 characters) — roughly two pages of written input. The entire report is designed to remain concise and well-structured, providing clients with essential information in a clear, easy-to-read format.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>Can I include my own disclaimer or terms in the report?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>Yes. You can add your firm’s or business disclaimer text in the <em>Professional Advice</em> section, ensuring it aligns with your professional standards and compliance obligations.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>Is this report considered immigration advice?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>The report compiles factual migration information from official sources. Any advice or commentary added within the <em>Professional Advice</em> section represents the subscriber’s professional input. This structure helps you provide tailored advice within a compliant, consistent framework.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="nectar-inherit-h3 toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>Can I brand the report with my logo or business name?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>Yes. Subscribers can upload their logo and business details, which appear on every report — presenting it as a professional document prepared by your practice.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>Will my clients be able to see that the report was generated through Anzscosearch?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>No. Reports are fully <strong>white-labelled</strong> for professional use.</p>
<p>Anzscosearch’s branding does not appear anywhere — only your logo and business details are displayed, making the report look entirely like your own.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>What makes this different from a standard occupation search?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>The Customised Occupation Report transforms raw search results into a structured, professional-grade document. It brings together data from multiple Anzscosearch tools and official government sources, applies the latest migration settings, and presents everything in a clear, branded format.</p>
<p>Unlike a standard occupation search, this tool lets you customise what’s included, add your professional insights, and generate a polished, client-ready PDF — all in one step.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div><div class="toggle accent-color" data-inner-wrap="true"><h3 class="toggle-title"><a href="#" role="button" class="toggle-heading"><i role="presentation" class="fa fa-plus"></i>Can I cancel or change my plan at any time?</a></h3><div><div class="inner-toggle-wrap">
<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
	<p>Yes. You can upgrade, downgrade, or cancel your subscription at any time. Access to the report feature will remain active until the end of your billing period.</p>
</div>



</div></div></div></div>
